parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become heavy, stiff, or loose, making it difficult to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels heavy
stiff
or loose
the vehicle pulls to one side
the steering wheel does not center itself
the vehicle is difficult to steer
the steering wheel moves by itself
the vehicle veers out of its lane.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the malfunction of the airbag, which can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of a collision.
symptoms: The airbag warning light appears on the dashboard
the airbag system malfunction message is displayed
the airbag may not deploy in a collision
the seat belt warning light appears on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt system can lead to the malfunction of the seat belt, which can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of a collision.
symptoms: The seat belt warning light appears on the dashboard
the seat belt is twisted and cannot be untwisted
the seat belt retractor is faulty
the passenger airbag is turned off with a passenger in the seat.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag sensor can lead to the malfunction of the airbag system, which can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of a collision.
symptoms: The airbag warning light appears on the dashboard
the passenger airbag is turned off with a passenger in the seat
the airbag sensor is faulty due to moisture or other environmental factors.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the A/C system can cause plastic particles to blow out of the vents, potentially causing respiratory issues or distractions while driving. In severe cases, the failure can lead to overheating of the electric hybrid battery, which can cause a fire.
symptoms: Plastic particles blowing out of the vents
check engine warning light illumination
particles blowing out of the vents while activating the A/C or heater.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the EME can cause the vehicle to suddenly shut down, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Sudden vehicle shutdown
no warning lamps or messages prior to the failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The overheating of the charging port can cause damage to the vehicle's electrical system, potentially leading to a fire.
symptoms: Charging port overheating
melting of the charging port.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration of the vehicle can cause loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: Sudden acceleration
failure of the brakes to engage.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Charging Cable and Fuel Pressure Sensor Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the charging cable and fuel pressure sensor can cause inconvenience, damage to the vehicle, and potentially lead to safety issues.
symptoms: Charging cable won't unlock from the car
fuel pressure sensor failure due to corrosion.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delamination of the carbon fiber roof can compromise the structural integrity of the vehicle, leading to potential safety risks, water leaks, and obstruction of view.
symptoms: The carbon fiber roof is bubbling
delaminating
or has chunks falling off
causing leaks within the main cabin
obstructing view
and potentially impacting other vehicles.
